{"title_page": "Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology", "text_new": "{{Infobox newspaper\n| name                = Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| type                = [[business]] [[magazine]]\n| format              = Paper and online magazine\n| foundation          = 1961\n| ceased publication  = \n| price               = \n| owners              = [[Scranton Gillette Communications]]\n| editor              = \n| founder             = \n| language            = [[English language|English]]\n| political           =\n| circulation         = 26, 242\n| headquarters        = [[Arlington Heights, Illinois]], USA\n| ISSN                = 1551-6091\n| website             = [http://www.dicardiology.com Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology]\n}}\n\n'''''Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology''''' is a trade magazine catering to [[cardiologist]]s and [[cath lab]]s.\n\n==History and profile==\n''Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology'' was launched by [[Chilton Company|Chilton Publishing]] in [[Philadelphia]] in 1961.<ref name=\"aus\">{{cite news|title=About Us|url=http://www.dicardiology.com/about-us|accessdate=19 February 2016|work=Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology}}</ref> In 1975 it was sold to Reilly Communications Group.<ref name=\"aus\"/> The magazine is owned by Scranton Gillette Communications.<ref name=itn>{{cite news|title=Imaging Technology News, Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology Capture Silver, Bronze ASHPE 2013 Awards|url=http://www.itnonline.com/article/imaging-technology-news-diagnostic-and-interventional-cardiology-capture-silver-bronze-ashpe|accessdate=19 June 2015|work=Imaging Technology News|date=6 May 2013}}</ref> Its focus is on [[interventional cardiology]], a branch of cardiology that uses catheter-based treatment to deal with structural heart disease. The magazine provides information about developments in this field<ref name=\"Columbia University Dept. of Medicine: Latest News\">{{cite web|title=Columbia University Department of Medicine|url=http://www.columbiamedicine.org/about/news.shtml|publisher=Columbia Medicine|accessdate=26 August 2013}}</ref> and is a notable publication within the healthcare industry.<ref name='FluoroPharma CEO Provides Shareholders With a \"State of the Union\" Communication'>{{cite web|title=FluoroPharma CEO Provides Shareholders With a \"State of the Union\" Communication|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/fluoropharma-ceo-provides-shareholders-with-a-state-of-the-union-communication-2013-07-29|publisher=Marketwired via COMTEX|accessdate=26 August 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology Recognized by ASHPE\">{{cite web|title=2013 Awards Competition List of Winners|url=http://www.ashpe.org/pdf/2013-winners.pdf|publisher=American Society of Healthcare Publication Editors|accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"What is needed for effective CDS software?\">{{cite web|title=What is needed for effective CDS software?|url=http://www.emergecds.com/2013/03/|work=Emerge Clinical Decision Solutions|accessdate=26 August 2013|archive-url=https://archive.is/20140901054057/http://www.emergecds.com/2013/03/|archive-date=1 September 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The magazine was the recipient of American Society of Healthcare Publication Editors award in 2013.<ref name=itn/>\n\nThe magazine had 26,242 subscribers to its print edition in July 2013. Melinda Taschetta-Millane is its editorial director.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.dicardiology.com Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology]\n* [http://scrantongillette.com Scranton Gillette website]\n\n[[Category:American business magazines]]\n[[Category:Cardiology journals]]\n[[Category:Magazines established in 1961]]\n[[Category:Magazines published in Illinois]]\n[[Category:Professional and trade magazines]]\n[[Category:Magazines published in Philadelphia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Newspaper\n| name                = Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| type                = [[business]] [[magazine]]\n| format              = Paper and online magazine\n| foundation          = 1961\n| ceased publication  = \n| price               = \n| owners              = [[Scranton Gillette Communications]]\n| editor              = \n| founder             = \n| language            = [[English language|English]]\n| political           =\n| circulation         = 26, 242\n| headquarters        = [[Arlington Heights, Illinois]], USA\n| ISSN                = 1551-6091\n| website             = [http://www.dicardiology.com Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology]\n}}\n\n'''''Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology''''' is a trade magazine catering to [[cardiologist]]s and [[cath lab]]s. \n\n==History and profile==\n''Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology'' was launched by [[Chilton Company|Chilton Publishing]] in [[Philadelphia]] in 1961.<ref name=\"aus\">{{cite news|title=About Us|url=http://www.dicardiology.com/about-us|accessdate=19 February 2016|work=Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology}}</ref> In 1975 it was sold to Reilly Communications Group.<ref name=\"aus\"/> The magazine is owned by Scranton Gillette Communications.<ref name=itn>{{cite news|title=Imaging Technology News, Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology Capture Silver, Bronze ASHPE 2013 Awards|url=http://www.itnonline.com/article/imaging-technology-news-diagnostic-and-interventional-cardiology-capture-silver-bronze-ashpe|accessdate=19 June 2015|work=Imaging Technology News|date=6 May 2013}}</ref> Its focus is on [[interventional cardiology]], a branch of cardiology that uses catheter-based treatment to deal with structural heart disease. The magazine provides information about developments in this field<ref name=\"Columbia University Dept. of Medicine: Latest News\">{{cite web|title=Columbia University Department of Medicine|url=http://www.columbiamedicine.org/about/news.shtml|publisher=Columbia Medicine|accessdate=26 August 2013}}</ref> and is a notable publication within the healthcare industry.<ref name='FluoroPharma CEO Provides Shareholders With a \"State of the Union\" Communication'>{{cite web|title=FluoroPharma CEO Provides Shareholders With a \"State of the Union\" Communication|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/fluoropharma-ceo-provides-shareholders-with-a-state-of-the-union-communication-2013-07-29|publisher=Marketwired via COMTEX|accessdate=26 August 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology Recognized by ASHPE\">{{cite web|title=2013 Awards Competition List of Winners|url=http://www.ashpe.org/pdf/2013-winners.pdf|publisher=American Society of Healthcare Publication Editors|accessdate=16 July 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"What is needed for effective CDS software?\">{{cite web|title=What is needed for effective CDS software?|url=http://www.emergecds.com/2013/03/|work=Emerge Clinical Decision Solutions|accessdate=26 August 2013|archive-url=https://archive.is/20140901054057/http://www.emergecds.com/2013/03/|archive-date=1 September 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> The magazine was the recipient of American Society of Healthcare Publication Editors award in 2013.<ref name=itn/>\n\nThe magazine had 26,242 subscribers to its print edition in July 2013. Melinda Taschetta-Millane is its editorial director.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.dicardiology.com Diagnostic and Interventional Cardiology]\n* [http://scrantongillette.com Scranton Gillette website]\n\n[[Category:American business magazines]]\n[[Category:Cardiology journals]]\n[[Category:Magazines established in 1961]]\n[[Category:Magazines published in Illinois]]\n[[Category:Professional and trade magazines]]\n[[Category:Magazines published in Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Media in Philadelphia]]\n", "name_user": "Hmains", "label": "safe", "comment": "category refine, sort sequence", "url_page": "//